this is the final page of Chapter 7
I feel like these chapters just fly along
each chapter is 26 pages like a standard US comic book
it's often padded out to look like 32 pages but thats because of ads
Do you ever find that constraint limiting?
nope- if a story portion doesnt fit you can always double the size to 52 and do a part 1 and part 2
sticking to a set number of pages per chapter makes it easier for determining printing costs and when i can make a new book
it also helps to know if i have a script that seems way too big for 26 pages - it's probably bloated and could be cut down
sometimes a constraint can be helpful!
the next chapter has some big action scenes- i could spend probably 15 pages doing nothing but action scenes- but that would be way too long
I'm torn on constraints. On the one hand they limit what you can do, but on the other hand they keep you from making something too crazy/random.
for me being new to these comics and streams its hrd to imagine that this is how comics are made

hmmm, ive never really thought of it as hard- you just imagine a story- spend a lot of time tweaking the major details- write scripts- form the scripts into how ever many pages per chapter- then draw scripts
